4.author: Matthew Iversen
4.content: Hey @everyone, just wanted to updated you guys on whats going on within the club at the moment. We are starting up preparation for our hackathon again (that hopefully doesn't get cancelled on us)  and we will be giving more details on it as we set them in stone. Additionally, we will be starting meetings up again in a couple of weeks once everyone is more set in their schedules. We will likely also be reducing the amount of weekly meetings to one during the school week and one every other Friday (aside from the project groups) in order to leave more time for workshop/project work. We still have plenty more in the works for you guys and we hope you have a smooth start to the school year!

29.author: Matthew Iversen
29.content: Hey @everyone, the next Friday meeting will be April 5th at 12:30 in BSTIC 104. A representative of Sabio Bootcamp will be coming to speak about the new partnership between us. This will include the bi-weekly series that covers the topics I'll mention in a second, potential trial bootcamp classes and the summer bootcamp/classes. This talk will be a great time to hear about their vision for improving IVC's CS curriculum and also ask any questions you may have.

30.author: Matthew Iversen
30.content:
Potential Topics (subject to change if you guys ask):
1) Git
2) Command line
3) Python applied to data science or machine learning
4) Connecting programs to a back-end
5) Mobile development
6) Memory management
7) React
8) Interview practice
9) Resume building
